==Translingual==
===Etymology===
presumably from the Cherokee name for opposum

{{wikipedia}}{{wikispecies}}
===Proper noun===
'''''Sequoia'''''
#{{botany}} a [[botanical name]] at the rank of [[genus]]. [[Circumscription]] and placement of the genus depend on [[taxonomic system]] and viewpoint. In the older literature this genus is assumed to have two species, but for the past few decades it is accepted as having only a single species - the [[redwood]]. Placement commonly is in [[family]] ''Taxodiaceae'' or, lately, in family ''[[Cupressaceae]]'' 

